<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.186664>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1 – 2. Habitus of Cercyon castaneipennis (1) and C. obsoletus (2). Scale bar 1.0 mm. Photographs by Th. Heijerman." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/186664/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.186665>
    dc:description "FIGURES 3 – 6. Elytral colour pattern and antennae of Cercyon castaneipennis (3, 5) and C. obsoletus (4, 6). 3 – 4. Elytral colour pattern, scale bar 0.5 mm; 5 – 6. Antenna, scale bar 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/186665/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.186666>
    dc:description "FIGURES 7 – 12. Male genitalia of Cercyon castaneipennis (7 – 9) and C. obsoletus (10 – 12), dorsal aspect. 7, 10. Basal piece and parameres; 8, 11. Penis; 9, 12. Sternite IX. Scale bar 0.2 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/186666/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.186667>
    dc:description "FIGURES 13 – 14. Distribution of Cercyon castaneipennis (13) and C. obsoletus (14) on a 100 km UTM grid. The record of C. obsoletus from northern Iran is outside the area shown." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/186667/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

